    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  We investigated potential SARS-CoV-2 tropism in human endometrium by single-cell RNA-sequencing of viral entry-associated genes in healthy women. Percentages of endometrial cells expressing\n                  <jats:italic>ACE2, TMPRSS2, CTSB</jats:italic>\n                  , or\n                  <jats:italic>CTSL</jats:italic>\n                  were &lt;2%, 12%, 80%, and 80%, respectively, with 0.7% of cells expressing all four genes. Our findings imply low efficiency of SARS-CoV-2 infection in the endometrium before embryo implantation, providing information to assess preconception risk in asymptomatic carriers.\n                </jats:p>",
